text: I didn't want to distract from the current discussion going on in the TAG Team channel, so this is as good of a place to bring this topic up as any. I, like many people, have recently cancelled Spring Break plans. As I was retracting my PTO request on TriNet, it occurred to me that the entire team is in the same predicament of not being able to travel (duh!), but this potentially raises two challenges. First, and most importantly, vacation is great for your mental health. Although we can't take traditional vacations at the moment, spending time away from from work is still very important to relax your brain and ease some of those everyday stresses. Therefore, I'd like everyone to take 1 day off during the month of April and you will not be deducted a PTO day. No, this is not an April Fools joke!!! Coordinate that day with Margaret to ensure we have adequate coverage across the team. Second, while I assume most people are not taking extended PTO over the next couple of months, I would encourage you to use some of your annual leave during this time to continue to get away from the daily grind of working and recharge your batteries. This will also relieve some of the strain on the organization assuming we get back to "normal" after the Summer and everyone is looking to squeeze in those vacation days before the holidays and the end of the year. We would hate to have to reject any such requests due to several others already being out of the office. All of this is a way to say that we're thinking about your short and long term well being. Stay healthy!!!
